            2: {
                title: "Augmented Reality in Construction – The Future of Building",
                content: `<p class="mb-4">Augmented Reality (AR) blends digital elements with the real world, allowing builders, architects, and engineers to see, interact, and modify designs in real-time on actual construction sites. AR overlays 3D models onto physical spaces, enabling precise visualization, clash detection, and improved communication between teams, reducing errors and rework significantly.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">On-site applications include visualizing finished structures before construction begins, checking alignment of MEP systems, and comparing as-built conditions to design specifications. Workers can see through walls to locate hidden elements, improving safety and coordination.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">AR also enhances training and safety by simulating hazardous situations without real-world risks. Remote experts can guide on-site workers through complex tasks using AR annotations, reducing the need for travel and enabling faster problem resolution.</p>
                <p>As AR technology becomes more accessible through mobile devices and smart glasses, adoption in construction continues to grow. Integration with BIM models creates powerful tools for quality control, progress tracking, and facility management throughout the building lifecycle.</p>`
            },
            3: {
                title: "What Are MEP Drawings in Construction?",
                content: `<p class="mb-4">MEP drawings are detailed plans that guide how these systems work together. They are like the instructions for assembling a complex puzzle, showing exactly where mechanical equipment, electrical wiring, and plumbing pipes should go. These drawings ensure coordination between different trades, prevent conflicts, and are essential for proper installation, maintenance, and future renovations.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">Mechanical drawings cover HVAC systems including ductwork, air handlers, and controls. Electrical drawings show power distribution, lighting, communications, and fire alarm systems. Plumbing drawings detail water supply, drainage, and gas piping systems with fixture locations and pipe sizing.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">Modern MEP drawings are created using BIM software, allowing clash detection between systems and integration with architectural and structural elements. 3D modeling reveals conflicts before construction, saving significant time and money compared to discovering issues on site.</p>
                <p>Quality MEP drawings include schedules, details, and specifications that guide installation and ensure compliance with codes. They also provide valuable documentation for facility operation, maintenance, and future modifications.</p>`
            },
            4: {
                title: "Bluebeam Revu vs PlanSwift – Which Estimation Software is Right for You?",
                content: `<p class="mb-4">In construction, digital tools like Bluebeam Revu and PlanSwift are vital in improving efficiency, accuracy, and collaboration. Bluebeam excels in PDF markup, collaboration, and document management, making it ideal for teams needing extensive review capabilities. PlanSwift specializes in rapid takeoffs and estimating, with intuitive tools for quantity calculations and cost analysis.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">Bluebeam offers powerful markup tools, measurement features, and Studio for cloud-based collaboration. It's particularly strong for design review, RFI management, and punch list creation. Users appreciate its intuitive interface and ability to work with large PDF sets efficiently.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">PlanSwift provides drag-and-drop takeoff, customizable formulas, and integration with Excel and QuickBooks. Its strength lies in speed - estimators can quickly measure areas, lengths, and counts while costs update automatically. The learning curve is relatively shallow for new users.</p>
                <p>Your choice depends on primary needs: choose Bluebeam for collaboration and document management, PlanSwift for dedicated estimating and takeoffs. Many firms use both, leveraging each tool's strengths for different project phases.</p>`
            },
            5: {
                title: "Mobile Estimating Apps – Bringing Flexibility and Efficiency to the Field",
                content: `<p class="mb-4">In the dynamic construction world, the advent of mobile estimating apps has marked a significant turning point. These tools bring unparalleled efficiency, allowing estimators to create and modify estimates directly on job sites. Mobile apps integrate with cloud platforms, enabling real-time data synchronization, instant quote sharing, and access to up-to-date material pricing, reducing turnaround times and improving accuracy.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">Field personnel can capture site conditions with photos, note hidden conditions, and request quote adjustments immediately. This real-time communication prevents costly change orders and keeps projects on schedule. Mobile apps also support offline operation in areas with limited connectivity.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">Integration with accounting and project management systems streamlines workflows from estimate to invoice. Data collected in the field feeds directly into cost tracking, providing accurate progress billing and cost control. Historical data improves future estimates with actual field productivity information.</p>
                <p>As mobile technology advances, features like AR measurements, AI-powered quantity takeoffs, and drone integration are becoming available, further enhancing field estimating capabilities and accuracy.</p>`
            },
            6: {
                title: "AI in Construction Estimation – Smarter, Faster, and More Accurate",
                content: `<p class="mb-4">Construction cost estimation plays a pivotal role in project success, influencing feasibility, budget, and profitability. AI and machine learning are revolutionizing this process by analyzing historical data, identifying patterns, and generating predictions with unprecedented speed and accuracy. AI-powered tools can adjust estimates for regional variations, material price fluctuations, and project complexity, continuously improving through feedback loops.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">Machine learning algorithms trained on thousands of completed projects can predict costs with remarkable accuracy, accounting for variables humans might miss. These systems learn from each estimate, becoming more precise over time and adapting to changing market conditions.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">AI also assists in risk assessment by identifying potential cost overruns before they occur. Natural language processing can extract information from specifications and contracts, automatically populating estimate line items. Computer vision analyzes drawings and site photos for quantity takeoffs.</p>
                <p>While AI won't replace experienced estimators, it augments their capabilities, handling routine calculations and providing data-driven insights for better decision-making. The combination of human expertise and machine learning produces the most reliable estimates.</p>`
            },
            7: {
                title: "What is Takeoff Software?",
                content: `<p class="mb-4">These days, the construction industry is being automated at a rapid pace. While there probably won't be replacements for laborers anytime soon, digital takeoff software has transformed how estimators measure quantities from blueprints. These tools calculate areas, lengths, and volumes automatically, integrating with estimating systems for seamless bid preparation and reducing manual errors significantly.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">Takeoff software allows users to import digital plans in PDF or CAD formats, then measure directly on screen using specialized tools. Measurements are automatically counted and can be linked to cost databases for instant pricing. This process is dramatically faster than manual scaling and counting.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">Modern takeoff software includes features like digital takeoff, assembly creation, integration with accounting systems, and cloud collaboration. Teams can work on the same project simultaneously, with changes updating in real-time. Version control ensures everyone uses current drawings.</p>
                <p>Benefits include reduced errors, faster bid turnaround, improved accuracy, and better documentation. Takeoff software also creates an audit trail of quantities and assumptions, valuable for change order negotiations and project closeout.</p>`
            },
            8: {
                title: "Best Software For Estimation",
                content: `<p class="mb-4">The success of construction projects lies behind accurate estimates because estimates need keen calculations. Top estimation software includes PlanSwift for takeoffs, Bluebeam for collaboration, ProEst for comprehensive estimating, and Stack for cloud-based solutions. Each offers unique features for different project types and team sizes, from small contractors to large enterprises.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">PlanSwift provides powerful takeoff tools with drag-and-drop simplicity, ideal for estimators needing speed. Bluebeam Revu excels in PDF markup and collaboration, perfect for design review and team coordination. ProEst offers complete estimating with cost databases, labor rates, and reporting capabilities.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">Cloud-based solutions like Stack and Buildertrend enable anytime, anywhere access with automatic updates and team collaboration. These platforms often include project management features beyond estimating, providing integrated workflows from bid to closeout.</p>
                <p>Consider factors like project types, team size, integration requirements, and budget when selecting software. Most vendors offer free trials, allowing evaluation before commitment. Training and support availability also influence successful adoption.</p>`
            },
            9: {
                title: "Benefits of Construction Software",
                content: `<p class="mb-4">Construction software marks a significant shift in project management, bringing digital automation to replace manual inefficiencies. Benefits include improved accuracy through automated calculations, faster turnaround times for bids, better collaboration between teams, centralized data management, reduced waste from material over-ordering, and enhanced ability to track project costs against estimates in real-time.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">Accuracy improves because software eliminates manual calculation errors and ensures consistent application of formulas. Historical data from completed projects feeds into new estimates, improving reliability. Real-time cost tracking helps identify variances early, allowing corrective action before small issues become major problems.</p>
                <p class="mb-4">Collaboration tools enable instant communication between office and field, with all project data accessible from any device. Subcontractors and suppliers can be invited to bid through portals, streamlining procurement. Document management ensures everyone works from current versions, reducing coordination errors.</p>
                <p>Financial benefits include faster bid turnaround enabling more opportunities, improved win rates through accurate pricing, reduced material waste, and better cash flow management through integrated accounting. The return on investment from construction software typically exceeds costs significantly.</p>`
            }
        };

        // Open modal function - defined globally
        window.openModal = function(articleId) {
            console.log('Opening modal for article:', articleId); // Debug log
            const modalOverlay = document.getElementById('modalOverlay');
            const modalTitle = document.getElementById('modalTitle');
            const modalBody = document.getElementById('modalBody');
            
            const article = articleData[articleId];
            if (article) {
                modalTitle.textContent = article.title;
                modalBody.innerHTML = article.content;
                modalOverlay.classList.add('active');
                document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
            } else {
                console.error('Article not found:', articleId);
            }
        }

        // Close modal function
        window.closeModal = function() {
            const modalOverlay = document.getElementById('modalOverlay');
            modalOverlay.classList.remove('active');
            document.body.style.overflow = '';
        }

        // Close modal on outside click
        window.closeModalOnOutsideClick = function(event) {
            if (event.target === document.getElementById('modalOverlay')) {
                closeModal();
            }
        }

        // Close modal with Escape key
        document.addEventListener('keydown', function(event) {
            if (event.key === 'Escape') {
                closeModal();
            }
        });

        // Theme functionality - wait for DOM to be fully loaded
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
            console.log('DOM fully loaded');
            
            const themeToggle = document.getElementById('themeToggle');
            const themeIcon = document.getElementById('themeIcon');
            const themeText = document.getElementById('themeText');
            const themeEmoji = document.getElementById('themeEmoji');
            
            // Check for saved theme preference or use default
            const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem('theme');
            const prefersDark = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
            const currentTheme = savedTheme || (prefersDark ? 'dark' : 'light');
            
            // Apply theme on page load
            if (currentTheme === 'dark') {
                document.documentElement.classList.add('dark');
                if (themeIcon && themeText) updateThemeUI('dark', themeIcon, themeText, themeEmoji);
            } else {
                document.documentElement.classList.remove('dark');
                if (themeIcon && themeText) updateThemeUI('light', themeIcon, themeText, themeEmoji);
            }
            
            // Add event listener for theme toggle if exists
            if (themeToggle) {
                themeToggle.addEventListener('click', function() {
                    toggleTheme(themeIcon, themeText, themeEmoji);
                });
            }
        });

        // Update theme UI elements
        function updateThemeUI(theme, themeIcon, themeText, themeEmoji) {
            if (theme === 'dark') {
                themeIcon.className = 'ri-sun-line mr-2';
                themeText.textContent = 'Light Mode';
                if (themeEmoji) themeEmoji.textContent = '☀️';
            } else {
                themeIcon.className = 'ri-moon-line mr-2';
                themeText.textContent = 'Dark Mode';
                if (themeEmoji) themeEmoji.textContent = '🌙';
            }
        }
        
        // Toggle theme function
        function toggleTheme(themeIcon, themeText, themeEmoji) {
            if (document.documentElement.classList.contains('dark')) {
                document.documentElement.classList.remove('dark');
                localStorage.setItem('theme', 'light');
                updateThemeUI('light', themeIcon, themeText, themeEmoji);
            } else {
                document.documentElement.classList.add('dark');
                localStorage.setItem('theme', 'dark');
                updateThemeUI('dark', themeIcon, themeText, themeEmoji);
            }
        }

        // Listen for system theme changes
        window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').addEventListener('change', (e) => {
            const themeIcon = document.getElementById('themeIcon');
            const themeText = document.getElementById('themeText');
            const themeEmoji = document.getElementById('themeEmoji');
            if (!localStorage.getItem('theme')) {
                if (e.matches) {
                    document.documentElement.classList.add('dark');
                    if (themeIcon && themeText) updateThemeUI('dark', themeIcon, themeText, themeEmoji);
                } else {
                    document.documentElement.classList.remove('dark');
                    if (themeIcon && themeText) updateThemeUI('light', themeIcon, themeText, themeEmoji);
                }
            }
        });

        console.log('Script loaded successfully');
    </script>
</body>
</html>